{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78b21d5c-09d2-455e-800d-e461bb1008b2","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for end-of-life runtimes. Two of your three targets are affected:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET (Core) side. You'd need to update those targets — e.g., replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`.\n\nBeyond framework targeting, MSTest v3 also has **API breaking changes** (e.g., some assertions and attributes were renamed/removed), so review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) after updating your TFMs.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a77518a0-1ae6-4139-9f81-b1a64d0e7fbe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important breaking changes regarding framework compatibility:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks**. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Core 3.1` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` — I need to check this. MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, so `net462` should still be supported.\n   \nActually, let me clarify the exact requirements. MSTest v3 supports `net462` as the minimum .NET Framework version, but for .NET Core and .NET, it requires `.NET 6.0` or later. This means `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't work with MSTest v3, creating compatibility issues for those two target frameworks.","outputTokens":685,"requestId":"480C:12EB87:629C204:6AECA8A:69FBFCE4"},"id":"0507d932-5d02-42b3-9e78-1819e9d809da","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:46:10.489Z","parentId":"ed8570af-5eae